import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['Miles_per_Gallon'], bins=20, color='green', alpha=0.8)
    plt.axvline(data['Miles_per_Gallon'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['Miles_per_Gallon'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['Miles_per_Gallon'].median(), color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['Miles_per_Gallon'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Miles_per_Gallon')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Miles_per_Gallon?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Year'])]
    data['Year'] = data['Year'].dt.year
    year_counts = data['Year'].value_counts().sort_index()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.bar(year_counts.index, year_counts.values, color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Year')
    ax.set_ylabel('Number of Cars')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of the manufacture year of the cars?')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
